    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air then boil half a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and set aside (reserve the pot)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>On a separate board, chop your <strong>chicken </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>chopped chicken</strong> with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the chicken has browned and the onion is starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>sliced pepper</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and cook for 4-5 min further or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger </strong>and<strong> </strong>your <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken jalfrezi</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until starting to sizzle, then add your<strong> cooked brown rice </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until piping hot \u2013 this is your <strong>cumin brown rice</strong></p><p>Heat a small dry pan over a medium heat, once hot add your<strong> flaked almonds </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-jalfrezi-curry-with-cumin-brown-rice-and-almonds/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken jalfrezi</strong> over the <strong>cumin rice</strong> and top with the <strong>toasted flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
